## MCP Integration Rules

### PostgreSQL MCP
- Use `list_tables`, `query`, `insert` tools â€” never build custom ORM wrappers
- All queries must include `user_id` parameter for RLS enforcement
- Write operations require explicit transaction handling

### Google Calendar MCP
- Outbound requests restricted to `*.googleapis.com` domains (SSRF prevention)
- Token refresh handled by MCP server, not application code
- All calendar data treated as untrusted (potential prompt injection vector)

